           SPELL=devilspie
         VERSION=0.17
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.burtonini.com/computing/${SOURCE}
        WEB_SITE=http://www.burtonini.com/blog/computers/devilspie
         ENTERED=20040618
         UPDATED=20040618
      SOURCE_GPG=gurus.gpg:$SOURCE.sig:WORKS_FOR_ME
       BUILD_API=2
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
        KEYWORDS="wm-addons"
           SHORT="A window matching utility"
cat << EOF
Devil's Pie can be configured to detect windows as they are created, and match the windows to a set of rules. If the window matches the rules, actions are applied to it. For example XChat can be put on all desktops by default or Aterm can be ripped of decorations by default (tested in OpenBox).
EOF
